## 6. Failure Mode Analysis

| Failure | Detection | Response | Recovery |
|---------|-----------|----------|----------|
| Router misclassifies intent | User corrects or seems confused | Ask: "It sounds like you want X. Is that right?" | Re-route to correct agent |
| Agent timeout (>30s) | Timer in orchestration layer | Return: "Taking longer than expected, let me try again." | Retry once, then fallback |
| LLM returns empty/invalid | Output validation (Pydantic) | Log error, return safe template response | Retry with simpler prompt |
| State corruption | Pydantic validation on every state write | Log corrupted state, reset affected fields | Checkpoint restore |
| Infinite loop | step_count > 5 | Force terminate, return partial result | Reset step_count, log trace |
| Memory retrieval failure | Empty vector search results | Proceed without memory context | Log for debugging |

